race.comment: Very tough race for punters to sort out. Leaning to MY PHAR LADY (9) who returned a very good figure when successful first-up over 1350m at the Beaumont track. Draws a lovely gate, drops 3.5kgs, and generally holds the form second-up so ticks all round. PIPERITA (10) showed a glimpse of form last time out when she worked home well to finish fourth over 1300m on the main track here. Suited by this slightly longer journey and with a little more improvement to come she is a definite contender. OFF THE PRESS (1) made it five top two finishes from as many runs this prep when a closing second over 1300m at Randwick recently. Yet to be tested over this trip but the last effort suggested a bit more ground would suit. CALTSAR (5) flashed home to just arrive in time when fresh from a spell over 1350m at the Beaumont track last start. Ran a couple of lengths slower than MY PHAR LADY on the same card. Each-way hope. STARRY DESERT (8) is a market watch first-up with McDonald aboard.
